  "texts": [
    "With Elisabeth Bik, a scientific integrity consultant, surmising that these examples merely represent 'the tip of the iceberg' (Stokel-Walker 2024).",
    "Another key development in this field of inquiry is the evidence that generative AI is being utilized in the academic peer review process (Liang et al. 2024b; Stokel-Walker 2024).",
    "A recent study exploring the language of feedback given to scientists contributing to AI conferences from 2023-2024 suggests that AI-generated feedback on scientific papers is evidenced in just this context when the language was analyzed (Liang et al. 2024b; Stokel-Walker 2024).",
    "The issue here according to Matt Hodgkinson, a member of the Committee on Publication Ethics, a U.K.-based organization focused on ensuring ethical academic research practices, is that AI-generated judgements are being intertwined with AIgenerated texts (Liang et al. 2024b; Stokel-Walker 2024).",
    "With reflection upon our theoretical discussion, it is important to note that scientific authorship, as a dynamic and autopoietic construct, is not isolated from its context."
